Last Broadcast Date: Thu 15 Oct 2009
Allegations of abuse by Zimbabwean refugees living in a South African church. A million jobs for people with autism? A Danish businessman explains how he's creating employment and transforming lives. Piracy on the high seas - the crew of a Ukrainian ship, held for four and a half months off the coast of Somalia, describe their captivity and eventual release. Show less